00:00:51.130 --> 00:00:52.830
Birmingham in the UK.

00:00:52.830 --> 00:00:55.940
And I've been spending the last
year, together with the

00:00:55.940 --> 00:01:00.650
ChromeVox team here, to make
an effort in order to make

00:01:00.650 --> 00:01:04.519
scientific material that's out
of the web accessible for

00:01:04.519 --> 00:01:06.480
people with visual
impairments.

00:01:06.480 --> 00:01:08.590
And first, we have concentrated
on making

00:01:08.590 --> 00:01:14.170
mathematics accessible,
using ChromeVox.

00:01:14.170 --> 00:01:15.830
Now why is that important?

00:01:15.830 --> 00:01:23.400
Well, one of the problems with
scientific material is that it

00:01:23.400 --> 00:01:27.180
is a hurdle in education that
many people that have visual

00:01:27.180 --> 00:01:32.340
independents are excluded from
having scientific material

00:01:32.340 --> 00:01:36.640
readily available as their
normal peers would have.

00:01:36.640 --> 00:01:40.840
Because it is much harder to
make scientific material fully

00:01:40.840 --> 00:01:41.510
accessible.

00:01:41.510 --> 00:01:43.290
And particularly, if you think
about something like

00:01:43.290 --> 00:01:47.450
mathematics, it is not as
straightforward as reading

00:01:47.450 --> 00:01:48.920
just regular texts.

00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:51.430
Therefore, it is often very
difficult to make it

00:01:51.430 --> 00:01:54.860
accessible using your average
screen reader.

00:01:54.860 --> 00:01:57.620
Now there have been a number of
efforts in order to make,

00:01:57.620 --> 00:02:00.120
in particular, mathematics
accessible,

00:02:00.120 --> 00:02:02.790
that are on the web.

00:02:02.790 --> 00:02:06.480
But these are generally efforts
that require either

00:02:06.480 --> 00:02:09.139
particular, special tools or
particular plug-ins for

00:02:09.139 --> 00:02:10.560
special browsers.

00:02:10.560 --> 00:02:13.680
So what we have been trying to
do with ChromeVox is make

00:02:13.680 --> 00:02:17.590
mathematics accessible in just
the standard screen reader--

00:02:17.590 --> 00:02:19.930
so making, effectively,
mathematics a first class

00:02:19.930 --> 00:02:24.400
citizen in the world
of accessibility.

00:02:24.400 --> 00:02:31.950
And we have done, also, in
addition, some special

00:02:31.950 --> 00:02:35.480
