00:36:00.080 --> 00:36:03.160
Now the problem with this
semantic enrichment is, of

00:36:03.160 --> 00:36:07.320
course, that this is a fairly
ad hoc procedure.

00:36:07.320 --> 00:36:14.820
MathML is a language which
primarily aims for display.

00:36:14.820 --> 00:36:19.140
So there's two types
of MathML.

00:36:19.140 --> 00:36:21.720
One is called Presentation
MathML, and one is called

00:36:21.720 --> 00:36:23.470
Content MathML.

00:36:23.470 --> 00:36:29.620
The idea of Presentation MathML
is that it takes care

00:36:29.620 --> 00:36:34.210
of how the math expression is
being laid out on the page.

00:36:34.210 --> 00:36:36.650
And this is what we're currently
working with.

00:36:36.650 --> 00:36:39.490
The idea of Content MathML is
that an author of a math

00:36:39.490 --> 00:36:41.600
expression actually puts
in some semantics.

00:36:41.600 --> 00:36:45.880
Unfortunately, that is hardly
available on the web.

00:36:45.880 --> 00:36:48.970
Therefore, what we have to
do is we have to take the

00:36:48.970 --> 00:36:51.840
Presentation MathML expression,
and interpret it

00:36:51.840 --> 00:36:55.000
in a way that seems
reasonable to us.

00:36:55.000 --> 00:36:58.200
Obviously, this can break
down in many cases.

00:36:58.200 --> 00:37:02.450
And therefore, the person who
actually knows best how to

00:37:02.450 --> 00:37:06.440
interpret a MathML expression is
generally the author of the

00:37:06.440 --> 00:37:08.200
expression, themselves.

00:37:08.200 --> 00:37:14.390
As a consequence, we believe
that it is very useful for

00:37:14.390 --> 00:37:17.410
people to actually be able to
customize the speech rules in

00:37:17.410 --> 00:37:19.510
a way that they will pronounced
the MathML

00:37:19.510 --> 00:37:23.370
expressions they write
in the correct way.

00:37:23.370 --> 00:37:29.790
We therefore, in ChromeVox,
offer an API to users out

00:37:29.790 --> 00:37:34.780
there, to authors of web pages,
to developers of EPUB 3

00:37:34.780 --> 00:37:40.130
readers that allows them to
define their own math rules--

00:37:40.130 --> 00:37:45.030
either override or add
to our rule base--

00:37:45.030 --> 00:37:47.890
in order to have math
expressions being spoken in

00:37:47.890 --> 00:37:49.380
the way they prefer.

